\example{elephant's statements (i.e., {{arxiv_2208_09292_FO0017||FO}}) are: (is largest land animal) and (has tongue). Positives of the siblings (i.e., {{arxiv_2208_09292_FO0018||FO}}) are (is amazing), (can jump), (has tongue), (has hoof), (eat grass), (can leap), and (is big animal). The negation set {{arxiv_2208_09292_FO0019||FO}} is then all the phrases in the siblings' set except for has tongue, which is a straightforward contradiction with positives about elephant.}